<item>
            <title>[LU-8224] Possibly access of bad pointer in mdt_obd_connect()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8224</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In mdt_obd_connect we have:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((data-&amp;gt;ocd_connect_flags &amp;amp; OBD_CONNECT_MDS_MDS) &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
            !(data-&amp;gt;ocd_connect_flags &amp;amp; OBD_CONNECT_LIGHTWEIGHT)) {
                atomic_inc(&amp;amp;mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_mds_mds_conns);
                mdt_enable_slc(mdt);
        }
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!test_bit(MDT_FL_SYNCED, &amp;amp;mdt-&amp;gt;mdt_state) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; data != NULL &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it&apos;s either we should drop the data != NULL check or also check it above or do something els.e&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise it just looks kind of bad and also confuses static code analyzers.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
